<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06311161 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06311161 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  FURNISHING; CHANGE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  BATHROOM tips from Joan Eisenberg, a certified designer in Baltimore:;  Separate the shower from the tub if possible. The shower door should open out.Place faucets on the wall away from the shower head to avoid being scalded.The ceiling should slope about 1/4-inch in a steam shower so condensation doesnot drip on the user.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Peninsula Home  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  IDEAS TO CONSIDER WHEN PLANNING BATH REMODEL  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Avoid sunken tubs or those with steps. They are dangerous to enter, hard toclean. The ideal tub should have a platform so one can sit down and swing thelegs in.;   Adequate water pressure is required for a low-flush toilet.;   Adream bathroom can include a dressing room, exercise area, linen closet andlaundry chute.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Washington Post  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Peninsula/Am  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911106  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  November  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  114  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday, November 6, 199100311161,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>